00:35:41,580 --> 00:35:44,280
So they just made that meme for good times,

760
00:35:45,081 --> 00:35:45,821
based on the art.

761
00:35:46,461 --> 00:35:48,641
I premiered it earlier in one of my first slides,

762
00:35:49,082 --> 00:35:52,722
but after you've been at Fantasy Flight Games for five years

763
00:35:53,103 --> 00:35:55,503
you get to put your face into a game,

764
00:35:55,803 --> 00:35:59,464
and it just so happened that my five year lined up

765
00:35:59,684 --> 00:36:02,005
right when we were starting development on Key Forge,

766
00:36:02,425 --> 00:36:05,926
so I'm the card, Quixo the adventurer, in quotes.

767
00:36:07,606 --> 00:36:08,166
Thank you very much.

768
00:36:08,406 --> 00:36:09,087
Thank you very much.

769
00:36:11,513 --> 00:36:14,974
Hi, my name is Mark from Creative Assembly in the UK.

770
00:36:15,414 --> 00:36:17,535
Having developed a game like Conquest

771
00:36:17,635 --> 00:36:20,657
in a very large, predefined world,

772
00:36:21,157 --> 00:36:23,478
and creating a game like Key Forge in your own,

773
00:36:24,278 --> 00:36:25,859
what do you find more enjoyable?

